# [B1] Key architecture per MASTER §8.1:
#   SUPABASE_KEY        should be the anon JWT key (eyJh... role:anon)  — respects RLS on DB calls
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY should be the service_role JWT / sb_secret_... — needed for private Storage reads
# Currently SUPABASE_KEY holds the service_role JWT which bypasses RLS.
# Storage reads work in practice because service_role can read private buckets,
# but set SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY explicitly and swap SUPABASE_KEY to the anon JWT
# before enforcing RLS on diagnostic_logs.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=eyJh...   # service_role JWT — fill in and uncomment